    Discordance between postprandial plasma glucose measurement and continuous glucose monitoring.
We discovered discordance between gold standard, fingerstick, and CGM in measuring plasma glucose concentrations after a meal. Consequently, emerging applications of CGM in healthy individuals, such as precision nutrition and diabetes onset prediction, may need to account for these discordances.Clinical Trial Registry 
