Prunes preserve hip bone mineral density in a 12-month randomized controlled trial in postmenopausal women: the Prune Study.
A 50 g daily dose of prunes can prevent loss of total hip BMD in postmenopausal females after six months, which persisted for 12-months. Given that there was high compliance and retention at the 50 g dosage over 12 months, we propose that the 50 g dose represents a valuable non-pharmacological treatment strategy that can be used to preserve hip BMD in postmenopausal females and possibly reduce hip fracture risk. Clinical Trials Registry Number  NCT02822378.
